From: optimized-package
Subject: [PATCH] Build against the conda ninja and limit nvcc to one thread

ninja is provided by the conda host environment, so it must not be pulled in
again from PyPI via install_requires. Also cap nvcc at a single compile thread
so build runners don't run out of memory during the CUDA compile.

--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -127,7 +127,7 @@


 def append_nvcc_threads(nvcc_extra_args):
-    return nvcc_extra_args + ["--threads", "4"]
+    return nvcc_extra_args + ["--threads", "1"]


 cmdclass = {}
@@ -383,6 +383,5 @@
     install_requires=[
         "torch",
         "packaging",
-        "ninja",
     ],
 )
